學科別分類



中文摘要

                  　　由於人類過度的開發，致使地球環境日益惡化，因此地球環境問題成為國際間重視的課題。建築產業如何降低CO2的排放不僅是建築界熱門的環保研究課題，未來更將是一種必要承擔的國際責任。掌握永續發展的精神，從建築物的出生到死亡，進行全面性、系統性的生命週期評估觀念具有宏觀的眼光，完整考量到每一個環節，整合性的評估建築物的環境衝擊與影響，是現代綠建築評估研究的重要觀念。本研究的重點係建立本土的建築物生命週期評估資料，以提供國內綠建築相關研究的重要基礎研究。藉由此建築物生命週期評估模式，我們得以在建築物建造之初即可計算出其CO2排放量，可對於建築產業所造成的環境破壞量化評估。並藉此期待能創造出低環境負荷量的綠色建築。本研究的成果摘要如下： 1.	進行本土化的台灣建築物生命週期評估盤查分析與基礎資料統計，此重要的基礎資料庫，為後續建築物生命週期評估源引的基本評估數據。 2.	建立台灣建築物生命週期CO2排放量評估法的計算流程與評估公式，建築物的CO2排放量計算值越低，代表該建築物越環保。 3.	建立台灣RC建築物軀體工程的CO2排放量簡算法預測公式，用以預測不同規模與建築類型之RC建築物軀體的CO2排放量，以科學化的CO2排放量數據討論建築物的環境衝擊程度。 4.	進行大規模拆除建築物的平均拆除年限調查，所推得之台灣地區建築物平均使用年限，對於我國都市更新計畫、城市規劃、住宅政策擬定均有相當的意義與幫助，可供為我國營建建設政策規劃的重要參考依據；同時也對於相關產業、企業界與學術研究上具有相當重要的參考價值與意義。 5.	由台灣建築物LCA案例模擬，得知台灣建築物新建工程之CO2排放比例偏低，而日常使用能源之CO2排放比例偏高，因此台灣的建築日常節能對策是建築生命週期CO2排放減量評估中最重要的部分。 6.	本研究建立建築物生命週期CO2排放指標LCCO2，該指標建立更明確與客觀的評估比較基準。我們得以分析不同設計手法對於建築物生命週期產生的環境負荷影響值，以求得最有效率的CO2排放減量對策。
                


英文摘要

                  　　As a result of mankind’s development，kinds of burden have already exceeded assimilative capacity of our environment. The environment problem has been a international issue. The major cause of the environmental problems are global warming and carbon dioxide emission. Before enacting an effective CO2 emissions reduction policy for the building, we have to establish a life cycle assessment for CO2 emissions resulting from buildings. The purpose of this paper is to establish a localized building life cycle CO2 emission database that includes materials manufacturing, materials transportation, construction, annual energy consumption, repair, reform and demolition, and waste treatment in Taiwan. From the information in this database, a LCA method for CO2 emissions of buildings will be developed.  　　In order to practice the goal of LCA, we also have to establish the local statistic of the buildings’ life cycle in Taiwan. This research had a large-scale investigation and statistic on building’s demolition in the four cities. We see that the average life span of the buildings which had been demolished in Taiwan between 1981~2001 is only 21.56~24.7 years. Compare with the life span of buildings in Europe and Japan, it is a very short time. The result of this investigation can help us drawing up the building policy and operating on LCA. 　　From the LCA research, it is known that the LCA for building’s CO2 emissions is deeply influenced by the local energy structure and the building energy consumption characteristics. In order to develop a dependable method for determining building CO2 emission for LCA, the foreign methods could not be directly used and it is required to establish an evaluation system with a localized building life cycle CO2 emission database. Through the estimation method, we could understand the condition of building’ carbon dioxide emission in Taiwan. And establish a forecast formula LCCO2 to charge a building’ environmental burden. 　　Because the everyday energy consumption accounts for large portion of CO2 emissions, the energy conservation strategy for building is not only the most important part in the LCA for building CO2 emissions but also the most efficient method for the building CO2 reduction policy in Taiwan.
                


